@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Angoes" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your
Workbench must have at least 8 colours.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Angoes runs fine
      on a 68000 machine, the game will require an Amiga with a
      68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To play, simply click on any angle (the "V" shaped thingies on
the game board), this will toggle its direction from left to right
or from up to down (or vice versa) depending on how it is placed.
If the angle is part of a series of 3 or more angles pointing in
the same direction, all the angles will be removed, and you will
get points according to the number of angles that have been removed,
as shown in the following table:

 3 angles:  1 point
 4 angles:  10 points
 5 angles:  100 points
 etc.

  Note that as long as the angles point in the same direction,
their colours do not have to match, but the amount of points is
multiplied by 5 if all the angles are of the same colour.

  As the angles are removed, the angles located over will fall in
the emptied spaces. If the fallen angles create series of 3 or more
angles pointing in the same direction, those angles will be removed
and you will get points accordingly.

  The game ends when it is no longer possible to make series of
at least 3 angles.

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the main window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

